message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Peru, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take you around 5-10 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Public transportation: Depending on the availability of public transportation in your area, you can check for buses or minibusses that pass by or near the grocery store. This option may take a bit longer due to stops and traffic, but it can be a convenient way to travel.

4. Taxi or rideshare: If you prefer a more comfortable and direct option, you can take a taxi or use a ridesharing service like Uber or Cabify. This will be the quickest way to reach the grocery store, but it may be slightly more expensive than other options.

Consider the factors such as weather, time, convenience, and your personal preferences to choose the best mode of transportation for your trip to the grocery store.
